dering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 10:56:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=359.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/oddnfun/wyrmbane_sml.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Reaver or other 2 HS?</span><hr size=1> <br>
I need to upgrade my weapon Severely.   Currently using an Arbitor's Combine at lvl 55.  Sigh.  <br>
<br>
Anyhow, I am trying to decide what I should get ot pretty much carry me from now through level 60.<br>
<br>
The reaver is a sweet ratio, but the non-magical may hurt me.<br>
Runs about 15-20k on The nameless<br>
<br>
Other options I am looking at:<br>
Tantor's Tusk  - about 8k on The nameless<br>
Worn Shai'din Naginata - about 5-10K<br>
Imperial Katana - not sure on price<br>
<br>
Just trying to figure out what would be the best to get?  I generally hunt with my Shaman roommate, and go on Epic hunts with my guild.   I rarely if ever do Pickup groups, but go to places with a full group of guildmates.    <br>
<br>
I really just want to be more effective since it seems like it takes forever to kill things.<br>
<br>
wyrmbane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udelsinionbarlepop.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Delsinion Barlepop</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 11:09:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=359.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lazykatcreations.com/images/Sdallas_small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reaver or other 2 HS?</span><hr size=1> Skip the tusk, you really won't be happy with it.  The naginata and katana are both pretty cool, kinda a matter of preference between the two.  A good option may be to try to get an exquisite velium weapon, they generally go on the cheap ( relatively ) and have good damage output.  You may also want to look into the argent protector, alot of people swear by them prior to NToV drops.<br>
<br>
As far as the reaver being non-magical, just carry a second gimpier magical weapon around with you for those instances when the reaver doesn't work.  I've never used anything but a magical weapon so don't really know how often this would effect you in the higher game so can't really shed alot of light on this situation.<br>
<br>
Essentially, if you are buying one, just go with an exquisite weapon.  You'll have more bang for the buck and can spend all that money on other stuff ( unless you can find the katana/naginata/ap at a good price ). &lt;edit&gt; This is assuming that you pass on the reaver due to the magical issue and/or you find a deal that you just can't pass up on one of the afore mentioned weapons. <p>"Let's get into trouble, baby"<BR><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=83637">Delsinion Barlepop: the pally</a><BR><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=83695">Elewood Ballues: the beastlord</a><BR><BR><a target="new"href=http://bladesandmagic.guildworld.com>Blades and Magic</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udelsinionbarlepop.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Delsinion Barlepop</A> at: 4/1/02 11:14:34 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukinammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinammer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 11:38:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=359.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Reaver</span><hr size=1> Trust me, dont go near the reaver. It sucks. Your best bet it to get a nice lance, 32/36, or 32/37 flavor. I play on the Nameless, and I sold my 32/37 for 4500p recently. <br>
<br>
At level 55, you will be hunting in plenty of dungeons and having to put away your fancy 20k weapon. That would really get to me, and seems pointless. <br>
<br>
Personally, if I had that kind of money, I would buy a lance now, and get a massive dragonclaw shard for 30k when I had the money.<br>
